1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Creamy Pesto Dressing
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Roasted almonds
1 packet Fine Breadcrumbs
250 g Pork Mince
1 packet Beetroot Relish
1 packet Currants
2 Radish
2 packet Potato
1 apple
piece egg
1 drizzle olive oil

• Set air fryer to 200°C.
• Cut potato into fries. Place fries into the air fryer basket, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and cook for 10 minutes.
• Shake the basket, then cook until golden, a
further 10-15 minutes.
TIP: No air fryer? Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C
fan-forced. Prep fries as above. Place on a lined oven tray, drizzle generously with olive oil, season and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice apple (see ingredients)
and radish.
• Roughly chop roasted almonds.
TIP: Reserve a few almonds to sprinkle on the salad!

• In a medium bowl, combine pork mince, fine breadcrumbs, the egg, garlic & herb seasoning, almonds, currants and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of pork mixture into meatballs, then flatten to make 2cm-thick rissoles (3-4 per person). Transfer to a plate.
Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the
ingredients and shaping the mixture into rissoles!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook rissoles in batches, until browned and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side.

• Meanwhile, combine apple, mixed salad leaves, and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil in a second medium bowl. Season to taste.

• Divide fruit n' nut pork rissoles, mixed leaf salad and fries between plates.
• Sprinkle salad with reserved almonds.
• Top rissoles with beetroot relish.
• Serve with creamy pesto dressing. Enjoy!
Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by spooning over the relish!